# Cursor context maintenance

When completing a task that changes project structure, update Cursor files in the same change set.

## Checklist

- **New route** → `Router.tsx`, `sidebaritems.ts`, `AGENTS.md` routes table
- **New feature app** → document in `AGENTS.md` architecture; add context/api/views pattern to `react-components.mdc` if novel
- **New layout or provider** → `AGENTS.md` + `routing-layouts.mdc`
- **New ui primitive or shadcn config change** → note in `shadcn-ui.mdc`
- **Tooling change** (scripts, build, deps, MCP) → `AGENTS.md` commands/stack line
- **MCP config change** → `.cursor/mcp.json`; re-run `npx shadcn@latest mcp init --client cursor` if needed

## Principles

- Keep rules under ~50 lines; one concern per `.mdc` file
- `AGENTS.md` is the detailed reference; `.mdc` rules are quick reminders
- Remove stale entries (deleted routes, renamed folders) when you touch these files
- Do not create extra markdown docs unless the user asks
